                                                 : CODE :
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public static void areaCircle(int n){
        int r = n/2;
        int a = (22*r*r)/7;
        System.out.println(a);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
       Scanner scn = new Scanner(System.in);
        int  n = scn.nextInt();
        areaCircle(n);
    }
}   

                                             : QUESTION :
                                             
Given the diameter of the circle as input, print its area.

For pi use 22/7 instead of 3.14 or Math.pi.

Also Area=(22*radius*radius)/7

Input Format

For each test case, you will get diameter as an integer input.

Constraints

1<= diameter <= 2^31-1

Output Format

Print the output in the integer format.

Sample Input 0

8
Sample Output 0

50
Explanation 0

8 is the diameter of the circle, so 4 is the radius. So area is 50.2857, but since we have to print an integer so we print 50.                                             
